<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>A half-dozen students, among them Juvenal Urbino, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="stood guard"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(守候)</code></b> for a time outside his residence on Avenue Eylau, and at the cafes where it was said he came <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="without fail"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(一定/必须/风雨无阻地)</code></b> and never came, and at last they sent a written request <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="for a private audience"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(私人会晤)</code></b> in the name of the angels of the Constitution of Rionegro.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She also brought back a cosmetic case that was the latest thing in seductiveness, and she took it to parties at a time when the simple act of <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="checking one's makeup in public"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在公共场合检查妆容)</code></b> was considered indecent.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And she <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="had a facility (for doing sth)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(对某事有天分)</code></b> for dealing with strangers that left her husband dumbfounded, and a mysterious talent for making herself understood in Spanish with anyone, anywhere.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>It was difficult to imagine anyone who could have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="assimilated the daily life of Paris"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(吸收/适应了巴黎的日常生活)</code></b> with so much speed and so much joy, and who learned to love her memory of it despite the eternal rain.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The child they had both longed for was born without incident <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="under the sign of Aquarius  \ ə-ˈkwer-ē-əs  \ 这里的 sign 是星座的意思"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在水瓶座的月份)</code></b> and baptized in honor of the grandfather who had died of cholera.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The same booksellers agreed to mail him the most attractive <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="scores"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(乐谱)</code></b> from the Ricordi catalogue, chamber music above all, so that he could not maintain the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="well-deserved"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(当之无愧的)</code></b> title earned by his father as the greatest friend of concerts in the city.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>As a consolation, Juvenal Urbino and Fermina Daza brought back the shared memory of a snowy afternoon when they were intrigued by a crowd that <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="defied"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(经受住/顶住)</code></b> the storm outside a small bookshop on the Boulevard des Capucines because Osca Wilde was inside.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She bought only one hat from Madame Reboux, but on the other hand she filled the trunk with sprigs of artificial cherries, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="stalks"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(梗/柄/茎)</code></b> of all the felt flowers she could find, branches of ostrich plumes, crests of peacocks, tailfeathers of Asiatic roosters, entire pheasants, hummingbirds, and a countless variety of exotic birds preserved <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in midflight, midcall, mid-agony"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(正在飞翔的、正在啼鸣的、正处于痛苦中的)</code></b>: everything that had been used in the past twenty years to change the appearance of hats.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She brought back a disturbing fragrance chosen from many at the perfume shop in the Bazar de la Charite, before the spring winds <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="leveled everything with ashes | level - to make flat or level"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(将一切夷为平地、烧成灰烬)</code></b>, but she used it only once because she did not recognize herself in the new scent.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Laferrière seemed less pretentious and voracious to her, but her wise decision was to buy her <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="fill of what she liked best | FILL - something that fills"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(她最喜欢的东西)</code></b> in the secondhand shops, although her husband swore in dismay that it was corpses’s clothing.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
